						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Slab lying in Survey No. 87.</hi></p>						

						<p>Bhūlōkamalla (Sōmēśvara III)—A.D. 1133.</p>						

						<p>This record is dated in the king's <hi rend="bold">regnal year</hi> (lost), <hi rend="bold">Paridhāvi, Māgha, [śu.] 5, Sunday,</hi> the details corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1133, January 13, Friday,</hi> instead of Sunday.</p>						

						<p>The inscription records a gift of land by Daṇḍanāyaka <hi rend="bold">Vaijanāthayya,</hi> the <hi rend="italic">perggaḍe</hi> of <hi rend="bold">Tarddavāḍi-nāḍu</hi> and Daṇḍanāyaka <hi rend="bold">Kalidēvayya,</hi> the <hi rend="italic">prabhu</hi> of <hi rend="bold">[Taḍavalage ?]</hi> for a tank.</p>						

						</summary>
